5: So let me get this straight...
8:
This metal man brought his world's
AI and robotic technology into this
world.
17:
And you recklessly released them
onto the streets as a way to develop
different AI programs.
23:
Right. Your combat AI and body
prosthetics are both the result of
incorporating his world's technology!
27:
And now... This AI, which the Lunus
Civil Police Force also uses, is
working with Themis and has
ordered the eradication of all heroes?
32:
Right! Quite the pickle, wouldn't you
say?!
37:
In all seriousness, this is troubling.
That AI has hacked all the other AI
and brought them into their plan.
41:
Wait... Does that mean all the
machines in the city are being
controlled by the Lunus AI?
45:
That's probably how they took
control of your body and shut you
down.
48:
Machines don't tire or complain.
They're efficient and easily replaced.
And above all else, they don't make
mistakes.
51:
That's the mindset of the people
who instituted these robots. Clearly,
they underestimated them.
55:
Then we need to do something
about that AI!
59:
Now wait a minute, Nate... Do you
think that AI is bad?
62:
If we leave everything to the AI, we
won't have to deal with the death of
a hero ever again.
66:
Above all else... An AI cannot be
swayed by emotions.
71:
Hm... I know a few droids that would
beg to differ on that particular point.
80:
Well, Nate? Do you want to continue
being a hero?
84: I don't know... but I'm just pissed off.
92:
Seeing that jerk Themis just makes
me wanna punch something!
95:
That's not the real Themis! She's not
even a real hero!
98:
Themis believed in others! He
wouldn't give up on us like that!
102: So what do you want to do?
107:
I've got some questions for her. So
I'm raring for a fight.
110: You've got a plan, right? Count me in.
115:
Yes, yes, that's the spirit! THIS is why I
chose you, Nate!
118:
Like the true hero that I know that
you are, be prepared to carry the
people's hopes and dreams with
you!
125:
Shall we go over the strategy one
more time?
129:
Ha, what's to go over? We're just
causing a distraction!
133:
What are you saying? No matter the
plan, we must all be on the same
page!
136:
But you have a point. Get your
target to go all out, and then nail
them right in the kisser!
140:
But don't lose focus, hero!
Remember, all you have to do is buy
us time while we dismantle the AI
remotely.
144:
That guy sure loves to talk. That was
a lot of words for "distract them."
149:
No kidding... Still, he's really counting
on me.
159:
To be honest... I feel like I'm gonna
hurl.
163:
But... I've got this. I know I can do it. I
won't run away.
168:
Now that's more like it! Heck, you
might be even more trigger-happy
than me!
172:
I am also impressed. Your firepower
far surpasses that of other organic
life-forms!
176:
Seraphim Form activated! Watch
out for any stray bullets!
180: Ditto! Now let's finish this ASAP!
186:
Ugh! There's too many of them! PBC
said we could send them the ammo
bill, right?!
191:
A-ahaha... Think we'll get hazard pay
for this?
195: All right, another one bites the dust!
199:
Hehe, how energetic. Can the rest of
you keep going?
204: Ah! Hey, no fair! That was my kill!
209:
Looks like you've got energy to spare
too, Hopper.
224:
Nate, how are the adjustments Regis
made to your prosthetics?
230: They feel great. Now... Let's go!
247:
Well... Looks like I can expect a visitor
shortly.
